<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - REMOVE AND INSTALL -
        THERMOSTATIC CONTROL SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>THERMOSTATIC CONTROL SWITCH</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure key switch and A/C switch are OFF.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower right instrument panel cover, heater-A/C assembly cover and drain tray.
                    Refer to REMOVE AND INSTALL,
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect two wiring connectors from the thermostatic control switch.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Before disconnecting wires, note circuit number locations to assure correct reassembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide switch from heater-A/C unit assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601636">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601636" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601636" filename="../figg16/g1601636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 36. Slide Switch From Heater-A/C Unit Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully pull the capillary tube from the evaporator core (
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601620.xml" xrefid="f1601635">Figure 35</hotlnk>) and remove the
                    thermostat switch.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully install the capillary tube through the hole at the base of the evaporator
                    opening into the evaporator (
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601620.xml" xrefid="f1601635">Figure 35</hotlnk>). Be sure to install in
                    evaporator to the same depth as before.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When the capillary tube is fully installed, connect electrical connectors to switch,
                    then slide switch into its holder on the heater-A/C unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601636">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower right instrument panel cover, heater-A/C assembly cover and drain tray.
                    Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
